			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">When my boyfriend and I first started seeing each other, I had a hard time being accepted among his friends.  I think it was just as hard for me to get used to them as it was for them getting used to me.  But you know, it finally happened.  Months and loads of working and crap later, we're getting along pretty okay.  I felt like I had finally been accepted.  Aside from the fact that I am the youngest of them at 19 and often get treated as such, it's been all right.  Now, on of my boyfriend's friends has just hurt me very badly and even after I talked to him, refused to apologize.
<br />

<br />
One of my boyfriend's best friends is now a person I can not bring myself to be around anymore.  This guy (yes, he plays EQ but I'm gonna call him X for his own right to privacy) is an asshole. i knew that and accepted him anyway.  I joked around with him, talked to him.  I always did my best to be a friend.  A few days ago I was over and his and another friends (A - Yet again for privacy) apartment and started playing Crystal Chronicles.  It is an awesome game in my opinion.
<br />

<br />
Now, A wanted to join in and it IS his game and game system, plus this guy is awesome.  So we were playin (thankfully, he has an extra GB Advance for me to use) and he invites X to play.  it's cool.  i get along with everyone as much as I can.  It was fine until X started to critisize my every move.  I seriously get into games, too but he was just downright mean.  So I put up with him making me feal like a worthless tagalong for a couple of days of playing this game, before I finally pick up a magic gemstone (which he had just told me not to pick up any) and I told him that I refused to drop it unless he gave me an apology for the way he had been treating me.  He said no, things got silent for a while, and A finally asked me to please drop it, so I did.  I wanted to play, too.  I was seriously lovin this game.  So I went over there earlier this evening and they were already playing.  I waited until they were at the map, where it would have been easy to add me in.  X told me to just wait a while.  
<br />

<br />
All I wanted was to play the game and hav fun.  So I told my boyfriend I was ready to go, then later told him what was wrong.  Being the emotional person I am....I cried.  I hate being treated badly by friends.  So he finally talked me into going over there, telling him what was wrong and asking for an apology again.  Maybe he didn't think I was serious yesterday.  I told him he would probably say no, in fact I was sure of it.
<br />
But after talkinga while, I went anyway.  Guess what he said......No.  So now I refuse to be around this guy anymore.  I will not let myself be around someone who is going to treat me like that.  Unfortunately this means I can't see my other friends over there.  They're supposed to be getting there own place anyway.  I'll wait until then.  I know that sounds wrong, but I seriously can't be around this guy anymore.
<br />

<br />
This is what I told my boyfriend..."I wish him a good life.  No one treats me like that.  I won't let them." 
<br />

<br />
What's so hard about saying "I'm sorry"?<br />_________________<br /><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=1104836" target="_blank" class="postlink"><img src="http://www.geocities.com/blackimmortalmusic/Sig.jpg" border="0" /></a></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
		</table></td>
	</tr>
