				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Ari looks lonely on that side of the fence so...
<br />

<br />
i feel i have to ask this, and i know i'm gonna get flamed hard on it but...as an honest opinion of yourself, do you possibly suck at this video game thing?  i'm not saying this to try to be mean or anything but like for example over thanksgiving i discovered my cousin sucks horribly at halo.  playing for fun hes ok cause i'm probably bored and i'm just screwing around and we talk and stuff.  playing to WIN tho...i'd be thinking up excuses to ditch him and get someone else on my team.
<br />

<br />
some people get more intense about games than others.  is hes super insanely good at it its entirely possible that he was trying to express that he thought you were screwing up his gameplay experience.  and since you were at his house, he probably expected you to take the hint and step out.  rude, yes...but maybe not intentionally mean.
<br />

<br />
instead you popped him into a corner by saying nothing for a long while, then out of the blue calling out his little bullshit routine on him.  and you got him with his other guy friend.  possibly you forgot but big cool guys don't cry or watch disney movies, or apologise in front of other guys.  so if he was in fact dropping the hint that he doesn't want to play crystal whatever with you, but you keep coming back / staying, then you stop the game to demand an apology for him not being happy about you staying...i'd be a little grumpy too to be honest.
<br />

<br />
not saying i can prove that.  but i'd say thats as good a read as the others.</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
